The paper deals with image to image translation, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN), which is a popular deep learning technique (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of object transfiguration and cross-domain semantic consistency losses, which are related to image segmentation and semantic labeling (cs.AI). The paper involves geometric changes across domains, which could be related to geometric transformations (cs.GR). Finally, the paper presents qualitative and quantitative experiments, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
